No ostentatious frame, but rather the quality of the surface reserved for bedtime, so the mattress and the box spring give a real base for a good bed.
They must of course complement each other harmoniously to please a concrete user.
During the choice several things are decisive,: weight, height, age, health status as well as gender of the owner.
The type of interior in which the mattress and the bed base will be placed is also important.
A typical example?
For example, in the country house where the latex mattresses are not continuously sleeped are not appropriate because they "warm up" gently.
In addition, they have a weight greater than the standard polyurethane mattresses.
It is necessary to return them frequently.
If they do not also have enough ventilation channels in the heart and if they remain, in addition, on a solid board, they retain moisture. Mold can also be formed.
Habit is also decisive in the choice.
Anyone who spends time abroad frequently using very thick mattresses with a softening layer, will feel difficult to feel well on a low and hard surface.
“That’s how all the Hokeyists who come back from NHL complain that they can’t sleep there.”
"For their tired shoulders, feet and ribs, they needed mattresses with a softening layer of lazy foam."
