That's why a few years ago the mattress with lazy foam conquered the hokeyists as well as other customers.
"Today everything is working well, Tempur, the Italian Magnifex but also the Czech Tropico have for example suitable mattresses.
You don't have to be a guy from NHL to be able to enjoy a lazy foam.
This "miracle" simply works.
It optimizes its rigidity and shape according to the heat absorbed or adapts to the heat of your body.
Nothing puts pressure on you and you won’t turn around in the night like after a tough game.
You just sleep better.
Lazy foam also works as a protection against squares.
For the choice of mattress according to your size, add the length of the feet, i.e. about 21/34 cm.
A man and a woman with a height of 180cm therefore need a bed of 210/220 cm.
The minimum width for each for a double bed should be 90 cm or a total of 180 cm.
For single-seat beds, singles for example, it is recommended to take at least 120 /140 cm.
It's convenient in case of a visit.
'However, it is a simple ruler for the width of the bed: when you are lying on your back you should lay your hands comfortably with the elbows slightly folded. Helena Prokopova, President of the Association of Executioners-Materchies and Decorators who has been dedicated for several years to the problem of healthy sleep and the ergonomics of furniture and teaches it in specialized schools.
For a double bed each needs its own bed base and mattress, so be careful however during the buy to choose the height of the mattress.
Otherwise you will only have to mount the box spring at different heights and this is not feasible on all the bed frames.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, spring mattresses at least 15 cm, of which count for the layer of shape and ventilation at least three centimeters.
"To the touch or sitting on the mattress you should not feel the springs," warns Héléna Prokopova.
Each mattress requires a well-defined type of box spring.
The bed-summer, when the mattress and the box spring are united like Siamese sisters, has nothing to do in the bedrooms.
The mattresses are very bad; it should not be washed, which is common today.
And since during the night one normally sweats from 0.2 to 0.75 l of sweat it is clear that after 5/7 years, the mattress begins to recall a large (and clogged) sieve.
For this, specialists refuse to advertise over a life of 25 years for a mattress or a lifetime guarantee.
But everything to his but.
And for this an experience advice from the sellers: for a mattress of 120/140cm, give up, for the covering of the mattress, hygiene or washing but rather add a protective mattress that you can easily remove and wash.
And even if nowadays it is common to make coatings with zipper for all the whole, that is to say that after the opening we have two parts (for the washing and the size of the washing machine it is very important!) otherwise the manipulation for the large models (and for a single person) becomes when we remove them a fight between a light weight and a heavy truck in a ring.
Do you have a rigid board in your bed instead of a box spring?
Never!
Maximum for a bed for visitors for one night only.
However, equip the board (if there are none) ventilation holes and use the spring mattress with a minimum height of 15cm with springs in bags (from Germany Taschenfederken) and a layer of aeration.
A polyurethane mattress should not be part of a bed of this type.
For single-position slatted box springs with 14/18 slats, latex mattresses or so-called sandwiches (maybe the combination of latex and coconut), are ideal but it will always be better for you to have a mattress with more slats, 28 and above, where the slats are lined in the bottom part of the kidneys and that it is thus possible to regulate it.
For mattresses in several positions it is not necessary to take spring mattresses because it does not respond to changes of position.
Next to the adjustment of the rigidity of the slats it is also possible to install what is also called a shoulder cradle.
It is a special bond of the slats that makes it possible to press or even tilt the slat so that the shoulder of the sleeper "fits" well.
For men who have "the shoulders as wide as the back", it's really an important thing.
