The Americans have a new "smart weapon"
The U.S. military sent a new "smart" weapon to Afghanistan, known only as the XM-25 code.
Generals believe that this new automatic rifle will have an influence on the conflict there with the Taliban and "will change the game" to their benefit.
The new weapon is like a super-precise cannon
Its projectiles are laser-guided with a precision of a few meters.
The special 25 mm calibre ammunition developed for this rifle and containing a highly shattering explosive, actually works like small grenades.
The munitions can be programmed in such a way that it will explode in contact with the target but also at any point in their ballistic trajectory.
It can therefore be used against an enemy hiding behind an obstacle, a wall or a ditch.
It is also not protected from above and when it falls on it a deadly rain of steel chips, it can put it out of combat too.
According to Richard Audette who took part in the development of the XM-25, the new rifle is the first infantry weapon that uses "smart" technology.
"The soldier uses it essentially in such a way that he finds the target, sends him a laser beam that determines the distance, thus obtains a precise point of sight, according to which he corrects his sighting site and presses the trigger.
"Let's say you aimed at 543 meters."
"When you press the trigger, the weapon loads and pulls at the distance of 543 meters more or less 1, 2, 3 meters," said Audette.
